============================================================================
djintegration - Continuous integration application for python
============================================================================

:Version: 0.0.1

Introduction
============

Django continuous integration is a tool for running and displaying continuous
integrations tests in you projects.

Although Django is used for this project this tools can be used by any python
project.

Installation
============

You can install ``djintegration`` either via the Python Package Index (PyPI)
or from source.

To install using ``pip``,::

    $ pip install djintegration


To install using ``easy_install``,::

    $ easy_install djintegration


If you have downloaded a source tarball you can install it
by doing the following,::

    $ python setup.py build
    # python setup.py install # as root


Register repositories to be part of the continuous integration
==================================================================

Here is how you register an application to be part of the continuous integration::

    DJ_INTEGRATION = [
        {
            'repo_url':'svn://http://code.djangoproject.com/svn/django/trunk/',
            'name': 'Django'
        },
        {
            'repo_url':'git://github.com/pinax/pinax.git',
            'name': 'Django'
        }
    ]
    